From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: deepak1556 <hop2deep@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 08:38:04 +0900
Subject: fix: disable mold for linux arm32

Keep mold enabled for Android ARM and Linux x86, x64, and ARM64, but
fall back to lld for Linux ARM32.

With mold enabled in https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/chromium/src/+/8040302
for non-official build, Electron startup crashes in _Unwind_VRS_Pop.
ARM32 uses EHABI .ARM.exidx/.ARM.extab unwind information unlike ARM64,
which uses DWARF CFI and is unaffected.

The failure involves mold ARM32 ICF and unwind-table handling, but
the exact linker defect has not yet been confirmed. Exclude Linux ARM32
until the issue can be isolated and fixed upstream while retaining the
link-time improvement on working architectures.

diff --git a/build/config/compiler/compiler.gni b/build/config/compiler/compiler.gni
index 1a25de82525af5f342040c92fe8cc00c0856800f..6d624032990084ed64d2d4afee9d7a3414c6c1ed 100644
--- a/build/config/compiler/compiler.gni
+++ b/build/config/compiler/compiler.gni
@@ -53,6 +53,8 @@ if (!is_win && !is_mac && !is_ios) {
         !is_official_build &&
         # Exclude Cronet because it crashes on dlopen(), see crbug.com/525305888
         !is_cronet_build &&
+        # Linux ARM32 binaries linked with mold crash in libgcc's unwinder.
+        !(current_os == "linux" && current_cpu == "arm") &&
         (current_os == "android" || current_os == "linux") &&
         (current_cpu == "x64" || current_cpu == "arm64" ||
          current_cpu == "x86" || current_cpu == "arm")
